metadata.name: Life has no scores #50
metadata.description:
We cannot compose life, at best we hum along to the melodies that life has been played in front of us. Looking back at the scores of our lives, the notations are never neatly noted, but fully felt.  Rewinding the songs of life are our memories, whether sad, happy, angry, or melancholy. It is not clear whether I am dreaming or awake, but our songs all do end. 

In this final drop (for ?), I have reused the first ever class calligraphy(){} I have written from my genesis drop “Nothing comes from nothing”. As time passes, 10 drops later, across almost to the year, I am grateful for the progress I have made, as an artist, and more importantly as a human. After all, what is behind the code of generative art is a human being. 

Scores of music, scrolls of calligraphy, calendar or diary, notating life, time passes, and changes are inevitable. Sometimes we sing louder in laughter and joy, sometimes we scribble in uneasiness, sometimes we just get lost in neon lights. Life goes on. You and me, all the same and yet different.  

There are too many friend artists, friend collectors, fxhash team members, to thank for helping me through this journey. I would like to pay homage to Rudxane in this work, who has taken me under his wings, mentoring and encouraging me in art as well as showing me some degen stuff on the side:-). This homage is not copy-minting, or copying of styles, which I do not have the coding skills to do so even if I wanted to. But it is the influence of taste in many works of Rudxane. In a vague but agreeable taste, I present to you Life has no scores. 

What I was taught was disrupted, and grid studies left unfinished, and oh do we have a BINGO?

Tested on Chrome. Other browsers may render different or not at all (firefox)

Press ‘2’ to save png.

metadata.name: SPOT #6
metadata.description:
A study of circles, sizes, lines, colors, grains and alphas. The composition consists solely of 2d shapes but generates a 3d look. The base colors use a random chromaticity factor which results in a wild range of combinations. There is a 70% change on a dark background and 30% on a light background also 15% change on black and white. 

Press s in live mode for a 2000x2800 download

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

Lammetje December 2022

metadata.name: 3ASF #10
metadata.description:
3 Armonografos Sobre Figuras / 3 Harmonographs on Shapes

"If I had to choose, the harmonograph is my preferred mechanism for making gen art"

The composition works with three harmonographs vertically distributed with 2 pendulums each that draw on black and white shapes. It is a game between the positive and the negative.

Steps-Layers:

1 - White or black background
2 - Draw shape 1 (triangle or Circle or Rectangle) with the opposite tone to the background.
3 - Draw shape 2 (triangle or Circle or Rectangle) same tone as the background.
4 - Draw the 3 Harmonographs. The (inverted) tones depend on the tones of the shapes and background.
5 - Cutting / glitch effect. Vertical and horizontal.
6 - Symmetries X or Y or XY or none are applied.
7 - Rectangles are cut again (yes/no)

// ---

"Si tuviese que elegir, el armonografo es mi mecanismo preferido para hacer arte generativo"

La composición trabaja con tres armónografos de 2 péndulos distribuídos verticalmente que dibujan sobre figuras en blanco y negro. Es un juego entre positivos y negativos.

Pasos-Capas: 

1 - Fondo blanco o negro
2 - Dibuja figura 1 (triangulo o Circulo o Rectangulo) con tono opuesto al fondo.
3 - Dibuja figura 2 (triangulo o Circulo o Rectangulo) mismo tono que el fondo.
4 - Dibuja los 3 Armonógrafos. Los tonos (invertidos) dependen de los tonos de la figura y el fondo.
5 - Se corta / efecto glitch. Vertical y horizontal.
6 - Se aplican simetrias X o Y o XY o ninguna.
7 - Se cortan nuevamente rectángulos (si/no)

// ---
Keys:

[1,2,3] -> change pixel density. Or can be passed via url ?pd=5 6000x9000pix. Be aware for the file size in render. 
[s] -> download canvas capture. Different pixel density, different sizes.
[double tap] -> download canvas capture on mobile

metadata.name: BlockonBlock #115
metadata.description:
‘BlockonBlock’ is the precursor and reserve pass for the upcoming ‘Hashway ‘69 Revisited’ collection by pixelwank. 
Free mint for pixelwank holders on tezos - After 3 days any remainders will be opened up to the public for 2tez.  

‘BlockonBlock’ was a study of rectangles following on from the use of circles in Generacci. 
Placements & building sizes are based on numbers from the fibonacci sequence. 

I had a blast making these and I hope they bring the collector as much enjoyment.

'Hashway '69 Revisited' coming soon :)

23 colour palettes 
14 colour overlays 
21% chance of extra lines
Click the image or press ‘s’ or ‘S’ in live move to save a 3000x3000 png 

Thanks for collectin’ & shoutouts to Circolors for the support <3 

R.I.F.F. 
Remember it’s for fun

metadata.name: Commune #69
metadata.description:
A minimalist composition with a nod towards architecture.

2932 bytes of Vanilla JS.

For more info, see article linked below: Me, Commune, Etc.

In live mode:
’S’ : save as svg (without grain)
‘P’ : save as png (3780x2673)

URL params in live mode:
‘g=n’ : no grain
‘g=w’ : wood grain
‘h=t’ : high resolution mode, 7560 × 5346 (Chrome only)

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save the png with those settings applied.
